        {
            "title": "GSK acquiring RAPT Therapeutics for $2.2 billion to advance food allergy breakthrough with long-acting anti-IgE therapy.",
            "id": "eec0ba11-fc36-4381-bc13-bfa9a7774236",
            "description": "GSK plc (NYSE: GSK) announced its acquisition of RAPT Therapeutics Inc. (NASDAQ: RAPT) for $58.00 per share, totaling an estimated $2.2 billion in equity value. After accounting for cash, GSK's upfront investment is approximately $1.9 billion. RAPT Therapeutics, a California-based biopharmaceutical company, focuses on therapies for inflammatory and immunologic diseases. The acquisition includes ozureprubart, an anti-IgE monoclonal antibody in phase 2b development for protection against food allergens. IgE plays a critical role in allergic reactions, causing 94% of severe food allergies. The current treatment involves injections every 2 to 4 weeks, but ozureprubart offers a potentially more convenient option.",
